	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Stpckholm - Danish police say they have evacuated an airport, public square and shopping centre due to a string of bomb threats. Police in Roskilde, just west of the Danish capital, Copenhagen, said they evacuated the local airport and a square in the city. They didn't give any details about the threats on Monday but said no one was injured. Meanwhile, police in Slagelse, about 60km southwest of Copenhagen, said they had evacuated a shopping centre there after a similar threat. Police urged people to stay away from the downtown area near the shopping centre. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  